---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Surgery — Entry Requirements" description="RACS SET surgical training entry requirements and selection process.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Entry Requirements</h1>
    <p>Surgery — RACS SET Program</p>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <h2>Eligibility Criteria</h2>
    <ul class="item-list">
      <li>Australian or Aotearoa New Zealand permanent resident or citizen at time of registration</li>
      <li>General medical registration (AHPRA <span class="tag">AU</span> or MCNZ <span class="tag">NZ</span>)</li>
      <li>Pass the <strong>Generic Surgical Sciences Exam (GSSE)</strong> before or by close of SET applications</li>
      <li>Complete the <strong>Introduction to Operating with Respect</strong> online course</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <h2>Selection Process</h2>
    <p>Annual competitive intake. Applications are scored and highest-scoring applicants are offered SET positions.</p>
    <ul class="item-list">
      <li>Applications assessed on CV, academic record, work experience, and referee reports</li>
      <li>Selection criteria vary by surgical specialty</li>
      <li>Competitive — number of positions limited per specialty and region</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <h2>Generic Surgical Sciences Exam (GSSE)</h2>
    <p>Must be passed as a prerequisite to SET entry. Covers surgical sciences including anatomy, physiology, pathology, and pharmacology relevant to surgery.</p>
  </div>
</Layout>
